The executive order issued on December 3, 2020, focuses on the use of artificial intelligence (AI) in the United States government. The purpose of the order is to promote the innovation and use of AI to improve government operations and services while fostering public trust and protecting privacy, civil rights, and civil liberties. The order establishes principles for the use of AI in the federal government and outlines policies for agencies to follow. These principles include ensuring that AI applications are lawful, purposeful, accurate, reliable, safe, secure, understandable, responsible, and traceable. The order also calls for the development of policy guidance by the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) to support the use of AI and directs agencies to create inventories of their AI use cases. Additionally, the order encourages interagency coordination and the recruitment of AI experts to work within government agencies. The order applies to AI used specifically for agency missions, decision-making, or providing public benefits, with some exclusions for defense and national security systems and AI embedded within commercial products. Overall, the order aims to promote the responsible and effective use of AI in the federal government.